criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  women in the age group of 18-24 years old;

          -  non-pregnant;

          -  having regular menstrual cycles with cycle lengths between 24 and 30 days;

          -  experiencing an average menstrual pain intensity equal to or greater than 5 on a 0-10
             Numerical Rating Scale; and

          -  scoring low (< 600 metabolic equivalent tasks [MET]/week) on the short-form of the
             International Physical Activity Questionnaire.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  women using oral contraceptive pills, hormonal therapy, or intrauterine devices;

          -  women using over-the counter analgesics during menstruation to treat
             dysmenorrhea-associated pain and experience no pain relief with those analgesics; and

          -  women participating in any formal exercise programme
